\displaystyle(3), a^2-c^2=2\frac{c\sin A}{\sin\angle ADB}\cdot b\cos\angle ADB
\displaystyle\implies \frac{\sin\angle ADB}{\cos\angle ADB}=\frac{2bc\sin A}{a^2-c^2}=\frac\triangle{a^2-c^2}
